text: The Garnavillo Township Culvert is a historic structure located west of Garnavillo, Iowa, United States. It spans an unnamed stream for . with On April 4, 1899 C.G. Stickfort and others petitioned the county for a bridge at this location. The Clayton County Board of Supervisors contracted with Josef Vogt of Guttenberg, Iowa to build this single stone arch culvert of native limestone. It is no longer in use, but remains in place west of Iris Avenue. The culvert was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1998. ==References== Category:Infrastructure completed in 1899 Category:Road bridges in Iowa Category:Bridges in Clayton County, Iowa Category:National Register of Historic Places in Clayton County, Iowa Category:Road bridges on the National Register of Historic Places in Iowa Category:Arch bridges in Iowa Category:Stone bridges in the United States
title: Garnavillo Township Culvert
